{% load static %}
{% load icf_extras %}
{% block header %}
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="{% static 'core/print_form.css' %}">
{% endblock %}
<div class="content">

  <div class="body">

    <div class="break-section">
      <h2 class="underline">Genetic information collected in the study</h2>
      <p>We will use your samples for genetic testing.</p>
      <!-- This testing will look at the genes that may be responsible for (explain in clear, understandable terms).</p>-->
      {% explain_text "whole_genome_sequencing" pd et %}
    </div>

    <div class="break-section">
      <h3>Where will you keep my information and samples?</h3>
      <ul>
        {% in_list "Biospecimen Collection" "research_features" pd as biospecimen %}
        {% if genetics %}
        <li>All of your genetic test results will be labeled with a code.</li>
        {% endif %}
        <li>Once we give your information{% if biospecimen %} and study samples{% endif %} a code, we will keep the key to this code in a locked file.</li>
        <li>Only these people and groups will be able to link it to you:</li>
        <ul class="checkmark-list">{% list_values "access_to_identifiable_info" pd %}</ul>
        <!--<li>We <icf-todo>[will also / will not]</icf-todo> put information about you from the study in your medical record.</li>
        <li><icf-todo>We will put a copy of this form in your medical record.</icf-todo></li>-->
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="break-section">
      <h3>Who will see my information?</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>We will protect your information as described in this form.</li>
        {% is_true "anonymized_info question" pd as phi_collected %}
        {% in_list "Genetics" "research_features" pd as genetics %}
        {% with coded=True %}
        {% if phi_collected %}
        <li>The local study team will know your name and have access to your information.</li>
        <li>We will do our best to make sure no one else knows that you are part of the study or can match the information to you.</li>
        <li>We will take your name off information and study samples that we collect from you during the study. We will give your information and study samples a code, so that no one can identify you</li>
        {% endif %}
        {% if coded or phi_collected == False %}
        <li>We also want you to know that even though we will give your test results a code, those results are unique to you. As technology changes, it may become possible for people to identify you from these results.</li>
        {% endif %}
        {% explain_text_li "aggregate data provided to sponsor" pd et %}
        {% if coded %}
        <li>But the sponsor will only see a code number instead of your name. </li>
        {% else %}
        <li>This will include your name and other information that can identify you</li>
        {% endif %}
        {% if coded and phi_collected %}
        <li>When we share the results of this study in reports, medical journals, or presentations, we will not include your name.</li>
        {% endif %}
        {% if phi_collected %}
        <li>It may still be possible for someone to identify you from the information you provide during this study</li>
        {% endif %}
        <li>There are people who make sure the study is run the right way. These people may see information that identifies you. They are</li>
        <ul class="checkmark-list">
          <!--<li><icf-todo>[Name of study sponsor or funding source]</icf-todo></li>-->
          {% list_values "access_to_identifiable_info" pd %}
        </ul>
        {% list_value "AR-Reportable_Disease_question" pd %}
        <li>State law requires that we tell the authorities if we learn about possible abuse or that you might hurt yourself or someone else.</li>
        {% endwith %}
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="break-section">
      <h3>Are there extra privacy risks because of the genetic testing?</h3>
      <p>{% explain_text "genetic_results_provided" pd et %}</p>

      {% is_true "genetic_results_provided" pd as provided %}
      {% if provided %}
      <p>Yes. Genetic testing may have special privacy risks. The main risks for this study include:</p>
      <ul>
        {% explain_text_li "genetic_results_provided" pd et %}
        {% if provided %}
        <li>Others may find out about your genetic test results and cause you to worry that your results will make it harder for you to get insurance or find a job.</li>
        {% endif %}
        {% explain_text_li "genetic_data_centralized_databases" pd et %}
      </ul>
      {% else %}
      <p>Yes. Genetic testing may have special privacy risks.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>

    <div class="break-section">
      <h3>How long will you keep my information?</h3>
      {{ pd.Length_Keeping_Personal_Info }}
      {{ pd.Length_Keeping_Samples_biospecimens }}
    </div>

    <div class="break-section">
      <h3>If I stop being in the study, what will you do with my information and samples that you collected while I was in the study?</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>We will be able to take your information and samples out of the study after it has started.</li>
        <li>If you wish to have your information and samples taken out of the study, call {{pd.primary_contact.title}} {{pd.primary_contact.name}} at {{pd.primary_contact.phone_number|phone}}.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="break-section">
      <h3>Will my information or samples from the study be used for anything else, including future research?</h3>
      {% is_true "use of samples or info for future research" pd as future_research %}
      {% if future_research %}
      <p>You must agree to this future use of your information and samples to be in this study.</p>
      {% explain_text "describe planned future use question" pd et %}
      {% else %}
      {% text_value "use of samples or info for future research" pd %}
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

